			</td>
			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">8bitMicroGuy wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Which microcontroller could be able to do this?<br /></div>Fast ARM or MIPS cores. (See also the Atari 2600 Harmony cart, which emulates the ROM too). Probably some of the fast dsPIC/PIC24 cores too. Basically anything that both 1- has an extremely low interrupt latency and 2- doesn't need to save a lot of state to handle that interrupt. (i.e. it doesn't do you any good if you stop executing the main code in 10ns if it takes 1µs just to save all the state before you can actually respond).<br /><br />I'd bet the various 100MIpS 8051cores would work too.<br /><br />Additionally, if you're trying to handle both PRG and CHR banking at the same time in the same hardware, your timing constraints get quite a bit more obnoxious.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

