				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Why do you want to use a microcontroller instead of something like a CPLD or FPGA?<br /><br />Like, the big advantage of a microcontroller is it can trade time for complexity. If your input/output can be serialized over time, or given latency, it's great for that kind of thing. Low frequency, high complexity.<br /><br />The bankswitching requirements are the opposite. High frequency, low complexity. Programmable logic devices like CPLD are cheaper and more effective for this, aren't they?</div>

