						<div class="postbody">MMC5-scale bank switching of all accessible tiles would need several kilobits of memory. In a CPLD, t each bit of memory costs one macrocell, plus some more for intermediate results, and to my knowledge, the CPLDs used in homebrew carts don't have nearly that many macrocells. With the 72-macrocell CPLDs on the infiniteneslives.com INL-ROM boards, it takes two just for a full MMC3 or FME-7. How much does an FPGA with enough block RAM for MMC5 ExGrafix cost again?</div>

